            "answer_text": "I would request you to follow the Ten Simple rules laid down for writing a review paper by accessing the info from the following link Ten Simple Rules for Writing a Literature Review To me writing a review paper basically involves doing extensive research about the existing subject which are already published. You can access online and offline libraries to find the required information. First of all list out the following Subject and Objective of the review paperMake list of the sources to tap.Access the sources and extract the finer points which you would like to include in your review paper with proper reference details.Once all the content is sourced. Create a draft paper based on your understanding of the topic and the content hierarchy.Once the draft is ready, read it thoroughly and may take help of your seniors if required to identify the unwanted material as well as define the order in which the content needs to be presented. Avoid too long or too short content.As per the defined hierarchy, organise the content.Think about adding graphical / chart / photos if possible to make the review paper more interesting.Ensure that your review paper summarises at the end your objective about the subject chosen.Present it with the right attitude and confidence about your task implementation.",
