            "answer_text": "A review is a critical analysis of something such as a book, a movie, a restaurant, or anything. You can see examples of these in the society section of the newspaper. Write your introductory paragraph with the thesis sentence stating your position about your experience with this book/movie/restaurant. Your body paragraphs will give details about this experience. It\u2019s a good idea to think \u201csandwich\u201d in your body paragraphs \u2014 tell some of the good, then tell what you didn\u2019t like, then tell a little more good. Conclude with a paragraph summarizing your opinion and your experience, perhaps with a positive view about how the weak points could be improved. (Example: \u201cThis restaurant has been open only two weeks; I\u2019m sure with time customers will see improvement with the problems I\u2019ve noted.\u201d ",
